concepts.term: In diagnostic US, the incident pulse can be up to 1 million times more than the echo pulse

triples.evidence: As the ultrasound wave travels through tissue, it doesn’t stay constant - it gets attenuated. That means the amplitude decreases gradually, and the intensity drops as the wave penetrates deeper.
